-- Turkish Foreign Minister Criticizes Germany's Ban on Charity, Vatan Says
-- Benjamin Harvey
-- 2010-07-19T07:02:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/turkey-criticizes-ban-on-germany-based-turkish-charity-ihh-vatan-reports.html

          
          
             Turkish Foreign Minister  Ahmet Davutoglu  criticized Germany’s ban of a Frankfurt-based charity
it said has ties to the Islamic militant group Hamas,  Vatan 
reported.  
 Davutoglu told reporters on a plane returning from
Kazakhstan that he had passed on his objection to the ban to
German Foreign Minister  Guido Westerwelle , the newspaper said.  
 The German government banned IHH on July 12, saying the
group provided support to Hamas “under the cover” of providing
humanitarian aid.  
